nl.strohalm.cyclos.entities.access

Class Channel

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.strohalm.cyclos.entities.Entity
      • nl.strohalm.cyclos.entities.access.Channel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Channel>

    public class Channel
extends Entity
implements java.lang.Comparable<Channel>
    A channel is an user interface to access cyclos functionality. There are some build-in channels, which cannot be removed, that represents the following channels:
    • The main web access
    • The wap2 interface (SERVER_ROOT/mobile)
    • The wap1 interface (SERVER_ROOT/wap)
    • The web-shop interface (SERVER_ROOT/do/external/payment
    • The pos-web interface (SERVER_ROOT/operator)
    Other channels may be registered at will.
    Author:
    luis
